snippet.title: CBC News: The National | Home stretch of historic U.S. election | Nov. 2, 2020
snippet.description:
After a tumultuous four years, American voters are hours away from the historic home stretch of the 2020 election. We are with the candidates at their final events, break down the challenges voters have faced and hear what the big issues are for Ottawa after this election. Plus, our U.S. political panel breaks down what to expect and what’s at stake Tuesday night.

#USelection
#BidenTrump

19:26 Ontario flu vaccine supply issues

23:54 What to watch for on election night in the U.S.

35:28 Will the 2020 election be a replay of Florida in 2000?
40:52 Johnny Depp loses U.K. libel suit
43:13 The Moment
